Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
get_metric(25.10)                                            get_metric(25.10)

Name
       get_metric - Gets the current state of metric(s)

Syntax
       get_metric

       -help

       [-branch <list_of_patterns>]

       [-exclude_inherited]

       [-id <id_name>]

       [-names <label_name>]

       <pattern_name>[-pending]

       [-pending_top]

       [-raw]

       Gets the current state of metric(s).

       You  can  use  this command to query the current state of any metric or
       metrics from the current specified list of metrics as well as a  previ-
       ous state.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each get_metric parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man get_metric

       -branch <list_of_patterns>
              Specifies list of patterns to match snapshot branches.

              This will limit all output to metrics stored in snapshots  whose
              branch  matches  the specified branch. This requires any inheri-
              tance to be re-run to exclude inherited values from non-matching
              snapshots.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -exclude_inherited
              Specifies not to return any inherited value.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -id <id_name>
              Specifies the database ID to output. Default  is  current  data-
              base.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -names <label_name>
              List of patterns to match snapshot names

              Name  of label to get metrics from (wildcards supported); no la-
              bel reports current metrics.

              Data_type: string, optional

       <pattern_name>
              Specifies the list of patterns to match metrics.

              Supports wildcard *. Use of * gets all metrics.

              Data_type: string, optional

       -pending
              Returns metrics from the pending (not yet created) snapshot.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -pending_top
              Returns metrics from the entire pending (not yet created)  snap-
              shot stack.

              Data_type: bool, optional

       -raw   Returns  metrics  as raw value (without normalization to defined
              units).

              Data_type: bool, optional

Related Information
              * encEnableMetric

